class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> largeGroupPositions(String s) {
        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        int start = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= s.length(); i++) {
            if (i == s.length() || s.charAt(i) != s.charAt(i - 1)) {
                if (i - start >= 3) {
                    result.add(Arrays.asList(start, i - 1));
                }
                start = i;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterates through the string once, tracking the start of each group and adding large groups to the result list. Efficiently handles the input string in a single pass.
